title: What Does the Georgia Runoff Mean for Control of the Senate?
description: Senator Raphael Warnock and his Republican challenger, Herschel Walker, are still neck and neck with less than half the vote. They will go to a runoff if neither gains 50 percent.
dc:creator: Derrick Bryson Taylor
media:credit: Audra Melton for The New York Times
media:description: Republican candidate Herschel Walker in Atlanta.
